  "detailedRequirements": "Previously, we have created a setup guide (<a href=\"https://github.com/appirio-tech/tc-common-tutorials/tree/master/submission-system\">https://github.com/appirio-tech/tc-common-tutorials/tree/master/submission-system</a>) to setup the whole submission system locally in Ubuntu Linux. But there are some problems to run it in Windows or Mac OS X.<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\">When trying to upload the submissions, the submissions API can not be reached.</span><br />\n<br />\nThe main cause is in Linux, it is directly running the docker service, while in Windows/Mac OS X the docker is running inside the default machine in VirtualBox. So there are two IPs - &nbsp;HOST_IP and&nbsp;DOCKER_MACHINE_IP<br />\n<br />\nso here are the general required changes.<br />\n<br />\n1. Update the nginx configuration (https://github.com/appirio-tech/tc-common-tutorials/blob/master/submission-system/docker/nginx/default.conf), to accept and use the two enviroment variables -&nbsp;HOST_IP and&nbsp;DOCKER_MACHINE_IP<br />\n1.1 for <a href=\"https://github.com/appirio-tech/tc-common-tutorials/blob/master/submission-system/docker/nginx/default.conf#L72-L75\">v3/submissions</a>, it should use HOST_IP.<br />\n1.2 for others, it should use DOCKER_MACHINE_IP<br />\n2. Build a new submissions:nginx-1.0 tag, and update docker-compose.yaml to use this new tag and environment variables.<br />\n3. Update the env.sh file to export HOST_IP and DOCKER_MACHINE_IP properly.<br />\n4. Update README.md file to include the changes and making sure the steps are accurate and works for Linux, Windows and Mac OS X.<br />\n5. &nbsp;Take videoes showing the new steps are working for Linux, Windows and Mac OS X.",
